<subSubSection pageId="110" pageNumber="506" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="110.[166,1373,284,553]" pageId="110" pageNumber="506">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,515,284,317]" pageId="110" pageNumber="506">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. TheJackass White-toothed Shrew is extremely rare, although it might actually seem rarer than it really is, if it is difficult to detect with usual tools. It should be noted that the “Armenian Shrew” (C. armenica) is recognized as a separate species and classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
